    <requireLicenseAcceptance>false</requireLicenseAcceptance>
    <tags>Resharper Macros</tags>
    <description>
        Live template macros for variables that:
        - Add or remove prefix and suffix; and
        - Transform the case
        - Provide a default value in case it resolves to empty
        Includes a simple macro which prefixes another variable with _ and makes the first character lower case.
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>
      Include a new macro which allows applying multiple (internal) functions at once.
      So you can remove something; make the first letter upper case; provide a default if the result is empty; add something; and remove something else.
      For more information on how to use it look at the project page (https://github.com/matthewvukomanovic/Vukomanovic.Resharper)
    </releaseNotes>
    <summary>Matthew Vukomanovic's commonly wanted resharper macro for easier chaining of variable declarations</summary>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency id="Wave" version="[9.0]" />
    </dependencies>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="bin\release\Vukomanovic.Resharper.Macros.dll" target="DotFiles\" />
  </files>
</package>